description:
Pfizer and BioNTech have said their COVID-19 vaccine is safe and highly protective in children as young as 12. Plans are underway to ask for emergency approval before the new school year begins in the US. Currently, the Pfizer-BioNTech vaccine is only authorised for people over 16. In a small study of 2,000 volunteers aged 12 to 15, no infections were found among those who received the vaccine. Levels of antibodies were also higher when compared to young adults.
